cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with a computer vision problem of crowd counting, which involves the use of deep neural networks for feature extraction and fusion. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method for feature fusion that involves the use of residual functions and multi-level fusion, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method in terms of performance metrics, which is a common theme in machine learning research (cs.LG). The paper uses three datasets for evaluation, which is a common practice in multimedia research (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a principled way of generating ground-truth density maps, which involves the use of optimization techniques, which is a common theme in numerical optimization and neural network training (cs.NE).
